I can still here Jeremy Irons saying, "You have no idea."

@Marshall Walthew 
I learned a lot of words from A Series of Unfortunate Events. "Ersatz" is my favorite.

The idea of spelunking while microdosing forcibly reminds me of The Descent, one of the scariest movies I've ever seen. To say it's EERIE would be an understatement.

@Lauren 

It has nothing to do with the film except for the title, which is the revealer for the puzzle. The theme is that you have to start the actual theme answer word from the inside (the gray squares) and then the rest of the word. For example, in 38A, you write in DI[SHIN]G, but the answer word is actually [SHIN]DIG, with [SHIN] being the letters in the gray boxes.

Welcome to tricky Thursdays.

@Vaer 

I had learned SEDGE from these puzzles, but then I forgot it: it's not a word I have ever or will ever use.

For Polish people - or this Polish guy - this was a Wednesday 🤣

